================================================================================
Notable Rust dependencies
================================================================================

The dependency tree is overwhelmingly MIT and/or Apache-2.0. Components worth
calling out explicitly:

- attohttpc — Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0).
  Pulled in transitively via `rust-s3` -> `aws-creds`. MPL-2.0 is a file-level
  weak copyleft: modifications to attohttpc's own source files must remain
  under MPL-2.0, but it imposes no copyleft on this project's code.

- usearch — Apache-2.0. A C++ HNSW index compiled and statically linked into
  the binary; permissive, no copyleft.

- ip2location (Rust crate) — MIT. Reads the IP2Location LITE database (see the
  data attribution below); the crate itself carries no attribution obligation.

GPL/AGPL note: the `lumis` syntax highlighter is configured WITHOUT its
`all-languages` default to deliberately exclude `lang-caddy`
(`tree-sitter-caddy`), the only GPL-3.0-licensed grammar in the set. Every
grammar that ships is MIT or Apache-2.0. See the comment on the `lumis`
dependency in the workspace `Cargo.toml`. If you upgrade `lumis`, re-verify
that no new GPL/AGPL grammar was introduced.

